gw.api.address

Class AddressOwner

  • gw.api.address.AddressOwner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    _proxy_.gw.lang.reflect.gs.IGosuObject

    public class AddressOwner
implements _proxy_.gw.lang.reflect.gs.IGosuObject
    Interface for a helper object passed to the standard Address input set. The helper object provides a way to set/get a single address on the enclosing entity (for example to set and get the primary address for a {@link entity.Contact}). It also contains information about which fields should be visible, required etc.

      Address Address
      Property for the address in the enclosing object. Marked as autocreate so that if the address starts out null then a Gosu expression of the form "owner.Address.State = someState" will automatically create a new address, rather than throwing a null pointer exception
      AddressFillableExtension AddressDelegate
      Delegate used to access address fields

      String AddressNameLabel
      Label to show for the AddressSummary
      boolean AutofillEnabled
      If true, autofill is enabled. Disable for search screens.
      boolean AutofillIconEnabled
      If true, enable the autofill icons. Disable for search screens.
      AddressCountrySettings CountrySettings
      Returns country-specific address configuration data
      Set<AddressOwnerFieldId> HiddenFields
      The set of fields that should be hidden, and not displayed in the UI
      boolean InEditMode
      Used to save the value of the PCF's CurrentLocation.inEditMode
      Set<AddressOwnerFieldId> RequiredFields
      The set of fields that should be required in the UI
      Country SelectedCountry
      Return the currently selected country; either the actual address country or the default country if the address is null
      String SelectedMode
      Return the string identifiying the PCF mode used for the SelectedCountry
      boolean ShowAddressSummary
      if true, show the address summary (when not in edit mode)
